cs.DL, cs.IR, cs.CR, cs.SE, cs.HC

The paper discusses self-archiving in computer science, which is related to digital libraries (cs.DL), information retrieval (cs.IR), cryptography and security (cs.CR), software engineering (cs.SE), and human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The focus on open access and copyright transfer agreements also suggests a potential fit with cs.CY (computers and society).
